==English==

===Pronunciation===
*kouch, /kaʊtʃ/, /<tt>kaUtS</tt>/

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg-es}}
# An item of [[furniture]] for the comfortable seating of more than one person.

====Synonyms====
*(''item of furniture''): [[divan]], [[settee]], [[sofa]]

====Translations====
'''furniture for seating'''
{{top}}
*Dutch: [[sofa]]
*Finnish: [[sohva]], [[leposohva]]
{{mid}}
*French: [[sofa]] {{m}}, [[canapé]] {{m}}
*Italian: [[divano]] {{m}}, [[sofà]] {{m}}
*Japanese: [[カウチ]] (kauchi)
{{bottom}}

====See also====
*[[armchair]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb|couch|es}}

# To [[lie down]]; to [[recline]] (upon a couch).
# To [[phrase]] in a particular style, to use specific [[wording]].
#:''He '''couched''' it as a request, but it was an order.''

